oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Swimming near the creek
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: People swimming at Walland with the covered railroad bridge in the background. Mrs. Bervalee Frazier Blazer (1881-1973) and Mrs. Joe Myers are in the far right, sitting on the shore. Bervalee's husband William Willett Blazer (1874-1949) and Winston Earl Blazer (1904-1992) are standing in the creek on the left. Joseph Jonas Myers (1883-1945) and Arlene Blazer are in the center standing in the creek. The other people pictured are unidentified.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
